history.content:
I've heard [a couple of years ago] that it's equivalent to more than six units and students should look at the syllabus before enrolling. 

CS 195 is a one unit course.

How is the workload of Engin 157AC? I heard it is more work compared to other humanities courses but it also satisfies three requirements. I already have AC completed but still need upper div H/SS and ethics. How does the workload of Engin 157AC (time needed for homework and exams) compare with CS195? Would it be advisable to take it with three technical courses (CS170 and CS189 included)?
history.subject: Engin 157AC vs. CS195
